<p>I do not understand the Searle factor here, there are so many first class American philosophers worth reading: David Lewis, Sydney Shoemaker, John Rawls, Hilary Putnam, Quine&#8230; Or was it a Searle seminar? What is the point?</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://pimm.wordpress.com">Attila Csordas</a>
 on January  5, 2008 <a href="#c3" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
